      • DUMMY_TABLE_NAME

        public static final java.lang.String DUMMY_TABLE_NAME
        The name of a table which can be use for SELECTS, but for which there is not a referenceable table to select from within the rule. This happens with rules that have only 'not' statements in their join clauses, as in a(5) if not b(*). Currently, the DSMRuleEngine must look for this table and populate it with a single integer before each evaluation.
